  <brief_title>Study of the Safety and Effectiveness of Rilonacept for the Prevention of Gout Flares</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Multi-Center, Randomized, Double-Blind, Placebo Controlled Study, Tolerability, and Efficacy of Rilonacept for the Prevention of Gout Flares During Initiation of Allopurinol Therapy</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Regeneron Pharmaceuticals</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Regeneron Pharmaceuticals</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a clinical research study to determine the safety and effectiveness of an
      experimental drug called rilonacept in subjects with gout who are beginning another
      additional treatment. Subjects will participate in this study for approximately 24 weeks.
      Rilonacept is being studied for use in preventing gout attacks in patients who have gout.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
